   <text>
      <body>
         <div type="letter">
            <pb n="1" facs="uoedh_hl_h.2802_1.jpg"/>
            <opener>


               <address rend="letterhead">
                  <addrLine>Ferne</addrLine>
                  <addrLine>Donhead</addrLine>
                  <addrLine>
                     <del>Salisbury</del>
                     <add place="below">Shaftesbury</add>
                  </addrLine>
                  <!-- added in pen -->
               </address>

               <dateline>
                  <date when="1923-11-10">
                     <hi rend="underline">10 <hi rend="superscript">th</hi> November 1923</hi>
                  </date>
               </dateline>

               <salute>Dear Mr. Hardy,</salute>
            </opener>

            <p>As President of the <orgName ref="#ps:AnimalDefenceAndAnti-VivisectionSociety">Animal
                  Defence &amp; Anti-Vivisection Society</orgName> I am writing to ask you if you
               would accept election as one of our Vice-Presidents? We are against all forms of
               cruelty <pb n="2" facs="uoedh_hl_h.2802_2.jpg"/>
               <milestone xml:id="m01" unit="reply"/>
               <!-- Check unit - reply rather than section?--> and are at this time specially
               pressing for reform <unclear>in</unclear> Slaughterhouses. </p>

            <p>I believe you are in sympathy with all our work for you wrote a charming letter in
               response to mine a year &amp; a half ago.</p>

            <p>With kind regards to yourself &amp; <persName ref="#ps:FlorenceHardy">Mrs
                  Hardy</persName></p>


            <closer>
               <salute>Yours sincerely</salute>
               <signed>Nina Hamilton</signed>
            </closer>



         </div>
      </body>
      <back>
         <div type="reply" hand="#ps:TH" rend="pencil">
            <!-- Not sure if it is TH's hand or secretary's and put in milestone for position -->
            <p xml:id="h2802a" corresp="#m01">[<choice><abbr>Ans.</abbr>
                  <expan>Answer</expan></choice>] <choice><abbr>Sh<hi rend="superscript"
                     >d</hi></abbr>
                  <expan>Should</expan></choice> be delighted if it does not commit me to absolute
               anti-vivisection..... Maybe cases in <choice><abbr>wh.</abbr>
                  <expan>which</expan>
               </choice> a very small amount of suffering, such as a human-being <choice><abbr>w<hi
                        rend="superscript">d</hi></abbr>
                  <expan>would</expan>
               </choice> submit to – may lead to enlighten­ment on some point of great value in
               relieving the future suffering both of men &amp; of the animals themselves So I don't
               know what to say. <choice><abbr>Pps</abbr>
                  <expan>Perhaps</expan>
               </choice> you <choice><abbr>c <hi rend="superscript">d</hi></abbr>
                  <expan>could</expan>
               </choice> suggest – say title "Animal Defence &amp; Controlled <choice><abbr>Viv <hi
                        rend="superscript">n</hi></abbr>
                  <expan>Vivisection</expan>
               </choice>
               <choice><abbr>Soc</abbr>
                  <expan>Society</expan>
               </choice>" or "<choice><abbr>A.</abbr>
                  <expan>Animal</expan>
               </choice> Defence <choice><abbr>Soc.</abbr>
                  <expan>Society</expan></choice>" alone &amp; I <choice><abbr>w<hi
                        rend="superscript">d.</hi></abbr>
                  <expan>would</expan>
               </choice> join – ...</p>
         </div>
